      • usePersistenceUnit

        public R usePersistenceUnit​(java.lang.Class<? extends PersistenceManagerFactorySupplier> factorySupplier)
        This method defines where (on which data base) query should be performed. WARNING!!! After the query performing the instance of DataBaseSteps keeps the given connection until another query is performed. This query should have another parameter set up by usePersistenceUnit(JDOPersistenceManagerFactory) or useDefaultPersistenceUnit(). Also it is possible to invoke DataBaseSteps.switchTo(Class) or DataBaseSteps.switchTo(JDOPersistenceManagerFactory) or DataBaseSteps.switchToDefault() for same purposes.
        Parameters:
        factorySupplier - is a name of dynamic persistence unit described by any subclass of PersistenceManagerFactorySupplier
        Returns:
        self-reference

      • useDefaultPersistenceUnit

        public R useDefaultPersistenceUnit()
        This method says that query should be performed on some default connection described by any subclass of PersistenceManagerFactorySupplier and its name defined by the property `default.persistence.unit.name`. WARNING!!! After the query performing the instance of DataBaseSteps keeps default connection until another query is performed. This query should have another parameter set up by usePersistenceUnit(Class) or usePersistenceUnit(JDOPersistenceManagerFactory). Also it is possible to invoke DataBaseSteps.switchTo(Class) or DataBaseSteps.switchTo(JDOPersistenceManagerFactory) for same purposes.
        Returns:
        self-reference
